wiki.content: This track ends the section of “Baby Pluto” songs and begins the “Renji” section of the album, one of Uzi’s personalities who they have described as being the more “sweet” and “nice” side of their personality. Since Renji is a reflection of Uzi’s softer side, the track is an apology to a past lover with whom Uzi’s relationship went sour. The line “that’s why you can’t fuck with fans” is a clear sign that this song is about Brittany Byrd, one of Uzi’s ex-girlfriends. They have discussed their relationship in many songs, including “20 Min” from Luv is Rage 2, where they tell the story of them meeting her in the crowd at one of their shows. The cover art of the first Luv Is Rage album is also a depiction of this happening. This song is an apology to Brittany, apologizing for potentially being misleading and letting their fame affect their relationship together. The Renji section of the album ends with “Prices,” with “Urgency” being the first song off of the album’s Uzi section. Uzi confirmed this on Twitter the day of the album’s release.
